p: Uncertainties in the projected baseline health effect estimates were moderate, based on recent trends. Age-adjusted renal hospitalization rates increased 30% over 12 years, from 100 per 100,000 persons in 2001–2003 to 130 per 100,000 persons 2012–2014. Trends in ED visit rates from 2006 to 2011 varied depending on diagnosis, with the steepest increase of 74% for septicemia [ 35]; but overall, ED visit rates increased 4.5% in this 6-year time period.
